## சென்னைப் பல்கலைக்கழகத் தமிழ்ப் பேரகராதி
ஆரத்தி
--
- āratti
- n. <</>ā-rati.
- 1. One of sixteen acts of worship, consisting in the waving of a light or lighted camphor before an idol;
- தீபாராதனை.
- 2. The waving of light, or water mixed with saffron, or saffron-coloured food-balls, before important personages such as a newly wedded couple, a ruler, or a spiritual head, in processions or on other auspicious occasions;
- ஆலத்தி.